WEBVTT

00:01.435 --> 00:03.668
♪ Da, da, Da-ba-Da, da, da,
Ba-da-Ba-Da-Ba ♪

00:03.703 --> 00:05.170
♪ Da, da, Da-ba-Da, da, da ♪
Let's go!

00:05.205 --> 00:06.872
♪ We'll be there ♪

00:06.907 --> 00:09.541
♪ A wink and a smile
and a great old time ♪

00:09.576 --> 00:11.743
♪ Yeah, we'll be there ♪

00:11.778 --> 00:13.845
♪ Wherever we are,
there's some fun to be found ♪

00:13.880 --> 00:16.181
♪ We'll be there
when you turn that corner ♪

00:16.216 --> 00:17.516
♪ We'll jump out the bush ♪

00:17.551 --> 00:19.217
♪ With a big bear hug
and a smile ♪

00:19.252 --> 00:20.853
♪ We'll be there ♪

00:26.248 --> 00:28.215
Narrator: This may look like

00:28.250 --> 00:30.751
another peaceful rural town
in America,

00:30.786 --> 00:33.554
but the McArthur family realized
their quiet neighborhood

00:33.589 --> 00:36.557
was actually a terror-hood.

00:36.592 --> 00:38.926
Meet Bobby Bateman.

00:38.961 --> 00:40.561
Sarah:
We thought he was normal,

00:40.596 --> 00:41.762
but then he kidnapped our cat,

00:41.797 --> 00:42.996
and he lit our house on fire.

00:43.031 --> 00:45.699
Those aren't normal things
at all!

00:45.734 --> 00:48.569
<i>Nobody could believe that he
would've done such terrible things.</i>

00:48.604 --> 00:49.770
Oh, man!

00:49.805 --> 00:51.572
Ho ho! No way.
This is messed up!

00:51.607 --> 00:53.674
<i>Narrator: The McArthur family</i>
<i>was left in the end</i>

00:53.709 --> 00:54.942
with barely anything...
[ Yawns loudly ]

00:54.977 --> 00:56.610
What are you watching?
Oh, hey!

00:56.645 --> 00:58.078
You guys gotta
check this out.

00:58.113 --> 00:59.780
I'm binge-watching
this crazy show

00:59.815 --> 01:01.348
about crime happening
anywhere --

01:01.383 --> 01:03.250
even nice places.
[<i> Woman sobbing</i> ]

01:03.285 --> 01:05.285
<i>Sarah:</i>
<i>We just didn't see it coming.</i>

01:05.320 --> 01:07.187
Wait, were you watching this
all night?

01:07.222 --> 01:09.256
Yeah, man. This show's insane!
I mean, look at him!

01:09.291 --> 01:10.691
You would never guess

01:10.726 --> 01:12.793
that this normal looking guy
would be so cray-cray.

01:12.828 --> 01:13.861
I mean look at me.

01:13.896 --> 01:15.129
No one knows
what I'm up to,

01:15.164 --> 01:16.930
but everyone assumes
I'm this perfect bear

01:16.965 --> 01:18.398
because of
my awesome looks.

01:18.433 --> 01:20.134
Well,
I heavily doubt that.

01:20.169 --> 01:21.034
You never know, man.

01:21.069 --> 01:23.971
[ Laughs ]
You never know.

01:24.006 --> 01:26.240
[ Large vehicle rumbling ]
Huh?

01:29.111 --> 01:31.245
Warren: You're the best.
[ Laughing ]

01:31.280 --> 01:32.913
Hey, hey, hey!
Check it out, guys!

01:32.948 --> 01:34.615
Looks like
we've got new neighbors!

01:34.650 --> 01:36.617
Oh! We've always
wanted neighbors!

01:36.652 --> 01:38.585
The barbecues,
the dinner parties!

01:38.620 --> 01:40.287
This is gonna be amazing.

01:40.322 --> 01:41.722
Ah! Let's go say hi.

01:41.757 --> 01:43.457
Ice Bear made casserole
for the new neighbors.

01:43.492 --> 01:45.993
Hey, neighbors!
Welcome to the neighborhood!

01:46.028 --> 01:47.728
Nice to meet you.
I'm Grizz!

01:47.763 --> 01:49.663
I'm Panda.
- Ice Bear.

01:49.698 --> 01:52.666
Hi, I'm Faye.
Warren. Pleasure!

01:52.701 --> 01:54.501
Excuse us if we're
intruding your space.

01:54.536 --> 01:56.069
Didn't know
someone was living here.

01:56.104 --> 01:57.671
No wonder
we're getting wi-fi.

01:57.706 --> 01:59.673
Hope you don't mind us
staying next to ya?

01:59.708 --> 02:01.108
Oh, of course not!
Welcome!

02:01.143 --> 02:03.277
We're so glad
that you guys are here!

02:03.312 --> 02:04.511
[ Laughs ] Heck!

02:04.546 --> 02:05.746
We'll just stay
forever then.

02:05.781 --> 02:06.947
[ Chuckles ]

02:06.982 --> 02:09.349
By the way,
are you a grizzly bear?

02:09.384 --> 02:10.651
Yeah!
Pretty cool, huh?

02:10.686 --> 02:12.920
Oh.
Your hair's so tough.

02:12.955 --> 02:15.022
Man, are you
as strong as you look?

02:15.057 --> 02:16.356
[ Chuckles ]
I look strong?

02:16.391 --> 02:18.525
Honey, you'd better
check this guy out!

02:18.560 --> 02:19.960
Warren,
don't be rude.

02:19.995 --> 02:22.329
What? I'm just admiring
his physique.

02:22.364 --> 02:23.664
Oh, I'm sorry, Grizz.

02:23.699 --> 02:25.666
We're just obsessed
with grizzly bears.

02:25.701 --> 02:27.167
I'm obsessed
with new neighbors!

02:27.202 --> 02:29.002
[ Laughs ]
- Come on. Touch the bear.

02:29.037 --> 02:31.605
Go ahead, touch him.
Warren, please.

02:31.640 --> 02:33.640
Well, it was a pleasure
meeting you all.

02:33.675 --> 02:35.542
Let's try and plan a dinner
sometime soon.

02:35.577 --> 02:37.477
Panda: That would be wonderful!
Grizz: Ah, that sounds good!

02:37.512 --> 02:39.546
All right, well,
we'll see ya around then!

02:39.581 --> 02:41.048
See ya!

02:42.184 --> 02:44.017
[ Laughs ]
Those guys were cool.

02:44.052 --> 02:45.986
Yeah.
- Ice bear forgot to give casserole.

02:46.021 --> 02:47.755
Oh, here,
I'll give it to 'em!

02:49.758 --> 02:51.391
Faye:
Did you see his size?

02:51.426 --> 02:52.626
Warren: The grizzly? Yeah.

02:52.661 --> 02:53.994
I like
how chubby he is.

02:54.029 --> 02:55.229
What?
I'm not chubby.

02:55.264 --> 02:57.231
I mean, this is what
we've been looking for.

02:57.266 --> 03:00.701
All the hard work we've put in,
finally paying off.

03:00.736 --> 03:02.970
Now, now, let's not get
too excited.

03:03.005 --> 03:05.405
Excitement
screws things up.

03:05.440 --> 03:08.075
We gotta make sure
- we capture him this time.

03:08.110 --> 03:09.643
[ Gasps ]
[ Pan rattles ]

03:09.678 --> 03:11.779
Who's there?!
Did you hear that?

03:13.548 --> 03:15.382
Huh?

03:15.417 --> 03:17.317
[ Panting ]

03:17.352 --> 03:18.218
[ Gasping ]

03:18.253 --> 03:20.087
What's going on?
They're after me!

03:20.122 --> 03:22.522
They're gonna kill me!
They're bear hunters!

03:22.557 --> 03:24.558
Calm down!
Who is after you?

03:24.593 --> 03:26.093
The new neighbors.

03:26.128 --> 03:28.161
They were saying stuff about
how perfect and chubby I was.

03:28.196 --> 03:30.264
And -- and how
they're gonna capture me.

03:30.299 --> 03:31.365
They have knives!

03:31.400 --> 03:32.099
Ice Bear has knives.

03:32.134 --> 03:34.334
Grizz, we all have knives!

03:34.369 --> 03:36.436
I think that TV show's
got you paranoid.

03:36.471 --> 03:37.604
[ Panting ]

03:37.639 --> 03:39.039
Yeah, right?

03:39.074 --> 03:40.607
There's no way
they're bear hunters.

03:40.642 --> 03:41.775
Yeah!

03:41.810 --> 03:43.076
[ Chuckles nervously,
sighs ]

03:43.111 --> 03:44.244
Dude,
those guys are cool!

03:44.279 --> 03:45.779
Ice Bear
knows who's cool.

03:45.814 --> 03:46.947
Yeah, you're right.

03:46.982 --> 03:48.348
Get some rest or something.

03:48.383 --> 03:49.283
We'll leave you alone.

03:49.318 --> 03:50.851
Uh, yeah. Okay.

03:50.886 --> 03:52.920
Yeah, that sounds like
a good idea.

03:52.955 --> 03:54.187
Here.
- Thanks.

03:54.222 --> 03:56.790
Okay, see you in a bit.
Yeah, cool.

03:56.825 --> 03:58.292
I'm -- I'm just gonna
take it easy...

03:58.327 --> 04:00.094
and relax.

04:01.663 --> 04:04.899
[ Snoring ]

04:05.968 --> 04:07.534
Faye: Oh, I just love
this little house.

04:07.569 --> 04:08.902
It's so cute.
[ Grumbles ]

04:08.937 --> 04:10.938
Panda: Oh, anytime!
Hey, what's going on?

04:10.973 --> 04:12.472
Hey, there you are!
What's up, Grizz?

04:12.507 --> 04:15.242
You looked kind of dead.
We didn't want to wake you up.

04:15.277 --> 04:16.643
Come, join us.

04:16.678 --> 04:18.145
Oh, hey.
[ Chuckles nervously ]

04:18.180 --> 04:19.613
I didn't know you guys
were joining us for dinner.

04:19.648 --> 04:21.114
Come on, big fella, sit.

04:21.149 --> 04:23.717
Be the meat
- in a Warren and Faye sandwich.

04:23.752 --> 04:24.651
[ Chuckles ]

04:24.686 --> 04:26.286
Dude, don't be rude.

04:26.321 --> 04:28.422
Uh, okay.

04:28.457 --> 04:30.590
Attaboy.

04:30.625 --> 04:31.959
Hi.
- I'm so excited.

04:31.994 --> 04:34.328
I've never sat next
to a grizzly bear before.

04:34.363 --> 04:36.096
[ Chuckles ]
Oh, yes, you have.

04:36.131 --> 04:37.931
Yeah, but that one
wasn't alive.

04:37.966 --> 04:39.666
Uh, that doesn't
sound awesome.

04:39.701 --> 04:41.001
Tell me, Grizz,

04:41.036 --> 04:42.903
what's it like living
in such an isolated place?

04:42.938 --> 04:45.572
I bet someone could scream
and nobody would hear us.

04:45.607 --> 04:46.807
We'll see about that.

04:46.842 --> 04:48.075
Scream.
- Huh?

04:48.110 --> 04:50.344
Yeah.
- I wan to hear you scream.

04:50.379 --> 04:51.812
[ Screams lightly ]

04:51.847 --> 04:53.914
No. Scream like
you're in pain --

04:53.949 --> 04:55.482
like your life
depended on it.

04:55.517 --> 04:56.850
[ Screams loudly ]

04:56.885 --> 04:58.418
Whoa!
Look at these teeth!

04:58.453 --> 04:59.519
They look so deadly!

04:59.554 --> 05:01.321
You wouldn't bite anyone
with these, though,

05:01.356 --> 05:03.156
like even when someone
attacks you?

05:03.191 --> 05:05.158
Uh, I -- uh, um...
Hey!

05:05.193 --> 05:06.593
Whose axe is this?!
Can I borrow it?

05:06.628 --> 05:08.695
Ice Bear would be happy
to hook up a neighbor.

05:08.730 --> 05:09.696
Awesome.

05:09.731 --> 05:11.198
[ Laughs ] Whoo!

05:11.233 --> 05:13.633
Really need this for
an important project we have.

05:13.668 --> 05:14.701
Right, honey?

05:14.736 --> 05:16.203
[ Groans nervously ]

05:16.238 --> 05:17.771
Okay!
It's getting kind of late!

05:17.806 --> 05:19.506
Late?
- Dude, it's only like 7:00.

05:19.541 --> 05:21.875
Yeah, Panda, brother,
this is when I go to bed!

05:21.910 --> 05:23.710
Oh? I respect that.

05:23.745 --> 05:26.947
We really need you
to be healthy.

05:26.982 --> 05:28.281
All right, guys,
thanks for coming!

05:28.316 --> 05:29.850
Please,
have a good night!

05:32.054 --> 05:33.220
[ Sighs heavily ]

05:33.255 --> 05:34.855
Panda: Dude,
- what was that all about!?

05:34.890 --> 05:36.356
What?
Uh, I was tired!

05:36.391 --> 05:38.558
You just woke up from a nap,
like, 10 minutes ago!

05:38.593 --> 05:40.894
Okay, fine! But you'll
thank me later, dude!

05:40.929 --> 05:44.297
Those guys are not the nice
neighbors you think they are!

05:44.332 --> 05:46.233
They're bear killers! Oh, man!

05:46.268 --> 05:48.001
You just ruined
our awesome dinner

05:48.036 --> 05:49.636
with our awesome
new neighbors.

05:49.671 --> 05:51.972
Enjoy the rest
of your evening.

05:52.007 --> 05:53.306
Pan Pan, dude!

05:53.341 --> 05:54.808
I'm just trying
to keep all of us safe!

05:54.843 --> 05:57.378
[ Door slams ]
You're welcome!

06:00.949 --> 06:02.849
[ Owl hoots ]

06:02.884 --> 06:05.586
[ Clock ticks ]

06:07.055 --> 06:08.889
[ Mumbles ]

06:08.924 --> 06:10.124
Hyah!
[ Glass shatters ]

06:13.595 --> 06:17.230
Just gotta stay...

06:17.265 --> 06:18.465
awake.

06:19.468 --> 06:22.236
[ Tapping ]
Gah! What was that!

06:23.271 --> 06:24.771
Oh, just a stupid branch.

06:24.806 --> 06:26.907
[ Soft chuckling in
distance ] Who's there?!

06:26.942 --> 06:30.310
[ Tapping continues ] Knock
it off, you dumb branch.

06:31.880 --> 06:33.113
Huh?

06:34.883 --> 06:36.550
[ Screams ] Stay back!

06:36.585 --> 06:37.517
[ Grunts ]

06:37.552 --> 06:39.719
[ Screams ]

06:39.754 --> 06:41.555
Aah!

06:41.590 --> 06:44.791
[ Panting ]

06:44.826 --> 06:46.393
[ Clang ]

06:46.428 --> 06:47.227
Huh?

06:47.262 --> 06:49.163
[ Clanging continues ]

06:52.000 --> 06:53.600
[ Grunts ]

06:55.070 --> 06:56.303
[ Screams ]

06:56.338 --> 06:57.304
Huh?!

06:57.339 --> 07:00.240
Dude, you should come
see this!

07:02.844 --> 07:05.446
[ Grunting ]

07:07.849 --> 07:09.149
I just don't know,
honey.

07:09.184 --> 07:10.650
You don't think
this might be a bit much?

07:10.685 --> 07:11.952
Not at all.

07:11.987 --> 07:13.386
I think it's just
what he deserves.

07:13.421 --> 07:14.921
Both: Huh?

07:14.956 --> 07:16.590
Oh, no! Our bones!

07:17.025 --> 07:19.693
[ Both laugh ]

07:20.295 --> 07:23.230
[ Grizz and Panda screaming ]

07:23.265 --> 07:24.598
Why do I have to be right
all the time?!

07:24.633 --> 07:26.266
Where's my phone?!
- We have to call the cops!

07:26.301 --> 07:28.135
We have to call the cops!
Panda, no!

07:28.170 --> 07:29.669
[ Grunts ]
What the heck, Grizz?

07:29.704 --> 07:31.004
No, we cannot
call the cops!

07:31.039 --> 07:32.572
In these scenarios,
they call the cops,

07:32.607 --> 07:34.141
but they never
nab the bad guys

07:34.176 --> 07:35.675
because they don't
have proof!

07:35.710 --> 07:36.843
Then what do we do?!

07:36.878 --> 07:39.112
We need to get
some evidence.

07:39.147 --> 07:40.680
I think
that was our last bag.

07:40.715 --> 07:43.116
Well, I guess we should
take a trip to town

07:43.151 --> 07:45.552
and get some supplies.
Good idea.

07:48.290 --> 07:49.489
Okay, they're leaving.

07:49.524 --> 07:51.725
How are we looking?
We're live.

07:55.730 --> 07:56.863
All right, you're clear!

07:56.898 --> 07:58.398
Good luck to you, brother.

08:11.313 --> 08:16.149
Ice Bear has never seen
this many knives.

08:16.184 --> 08:18.018
Look at that!
Now can we call the cops?!

08:18.053 --> 08:19.352
It's not good enough.

08:19.387 --> 08:21.088
We need something
really incriminating.

08:22.057 --> 08:23.757
[ Gasps]

08:28.196 --> 08:29.829
Is that enough evidence?

08:29.864 --> 08:31.498
Yeah,
that's enough evidence.

08:32.667 --> 08:33.767
[ Clangs ]

08:35.537 --> 08:37.170
What! - Oh, no! What happened?!

08:37.205 --> 08:38.572
I don't know!
We lost the feed!

08:38.607 --> 08:40.574
Stay here and keep watch.
I'm going in!

08:41.843 --> 08:43.176
[ Panting ]

08:43.211 --> 08:44.377
Brother,
are you okay, dude?!

08:44.412 --> 08:45.879
What happened?!
What'd you see?!

08:45.914 --> 08:47.614
Ice Bear saw that.

08:54.856 --> 08:56.089
They're after
all three of us.

08:56.124 --> 08:57.591
Guys!
- [ Screams ]

08:57.626 --> 08:58.692
What are you doing?!

08:58.727 --> 09:00.193
You're supposed to be
keeping watch!

09:00.228 --> 09:01.761
I got too scared and --
whoa!

09:01.796 --> 09:03.096
Are those pictures of me?

09:03.131 --> 09:04.764
Dude,
those are pictures of me!

09:04.799 --> 09:06.366
[ Warren and Faye laughing ]

09:06.401 --> 09:08.835
Warren: That's the fastest
supply trip we've ever made!

09:08.870 --> 09:11.104
Oh, no, they're coming!
Quick, in that closet!

09:11.139 --> 09:12.239
We'll hide in here until --

09:12.274 --> 09:13.106
[ All screaming ]

09:13.141 --> 09:14.174
Grizz: Oh, no!

09:14.209 --> 09:16.743
This is a madhouse!

09:16.778 --> 09:18.111
Other door!

09:19.080 --> 09:20.781
Uh...
the window, quick!

09:22.484 --> 09:23.617
[ Grunts ]

09:24.419 --> 09:26.253
Whoa, whoa! [ Grunts ]

09:26.288 --> 09:27.454
Warren:
Hey, is someone in here?

09:27.489 --> 09:29.022
Faye: The skeleton's
on the floor.

09:29.057 --> 09:31.391
Honey,
I think we have company.

09:32.127 --> 09:33.293
[ Grunting ]

09:33.328 --> 09:34.961
Oh, no, I'm stuck!

09:34.996 --> 09:36.396
Grizz, we'll get you
out of there!

09:36.431 --> 09:38.865
Oh, they're right.
I am too chubby!

09:38.900 --> 09:40.100
Is someone in there?

09:40.135 --> 09:41.868
We're coming in
on the count of three.

09:41.903 --> 09:43.970
Okay, one, two...

09:44.005 --> 09:45.472
Three!
- ...Three!

09:47.275 --> 09:48.975
What is going on here!?

09:49.010 --> 09:51.077
Stay back!
We know what you are!

09:51.112 --> 09:52.312
[ Grunting ]

09:52.347 --> 09:53.980
We know
you're bear hunters!

09:54.015 --> 09:55.649
Both: Bear hunters?!

09:55.684 --> 09:56.650
They're on to us, honey.

09:56.685 --> 09:58.118
Should we tell them
who we are?

09:58.153 --> 10:00.087
I think it's better
if we show them.

10:00.955 --> 10:02.122
[ All gasp ]

10:02.157 --> 10:03.857
We're not bear hunters...

10:05.126 --> 10:07.627
We're bear carvers!

10:07.662 --> 10:10.063
Uh, it's me.

10:10.098 --> 10:11.164
I'm glad you think so!

10:11.199 --> 10:12.332
We've been
studying you a lot

10:12.367 --> 10:13.800
trying to get the likeness
right!

10:13.835 --> 10:16.002
My husband and I
- run a woodworking business,

10:16.037 --> 10:17.437
and when we met you guys,

10:17.472 --> 10:19.306
we thought you were
- perfect muses for our work.

10:19.341 --> 10:21.241
We tried to be
inconspicuous.

10:21.276 --> 10:23.476
We didn't want
to freak you guys out.

10:23.511 --> 10:25.178
But what about
the bones?

10:25.213 --> 10:26.346
Those were fake.

10:26.381 --> 10:27.981
We study them
for reference.

10:28.016 --> 10:30.016
That all makes
perfect sense.

10:30.051 --> 10:31.418
I'm so sorry
I misjudged you.

10:31.453 --> 10:32.819
I let my imagination
run wild,

10:32.854 --> 10:34.688
and then I dragged
my brothers into it.

10:34.723 --> 10:37.023
Not to mention,
we destroyed your RV.

10:37.058 --> 10:38.358
Oh, I feel terrible.

10:38.393 --> 10:40.126
I wish there was
something we could do

10:40.161 --> 10:41.161
to make it up to you.

10:41.196 --> 10:42.529
Hmm.
- Hmm.

10:42.564 --> 10:45.165
Well,
there is one thing...

10:45.200 --> 10:47.834
♪♪

10:47.869 --> 10:50.036
How much longer
do we need to do this?

10:50.071 --> 10:51.304
My contacts
are drying out.

10:51.339 --> 10:52.806
Ice Bear
can't feel his butt.

10:52.841 --> 10:54.441
Faye: Don't move!

10:54.476 --> 10:56.609
You guys are doing great!
- [ Chuckles ]

10:56.644 --> 10:58.044
Yeah,
just a few more hours,

10:58.079 --> 11:00.847
and I think we'll have
all the carvings we need!

11:00.882 --> 11:02.716
[ Laughs ]

11:04.919 --> 11:08.155
♪♪

11:17.665 --> 11:19.333
Done!
- Done!        Done!
